{"author": "Bob Marley", "text": "If she's amazing, she won't be easy. If she's easy, she won't be amazing. If she's worth it, you wont give up. If you give up, you're not worthy. ... Truth is, everybody is going to hurt you; you just gotta find the ones worth suffering for.", "tags": ["inspirational", "love"]}
{"author": "Albert Camus", "text": "Live to the point of tears.", "tags": ["life", "living"]}
{"author": "Jerry Seinfeld", "text": "If a book about failures doesn't sell, is it a success?", "tags": ["books", "funny"]}
{"author": "Lauren Oliver", "text": "Maybe you can afford to wait. Maybe for you there's a tomorrow. Maybe for you there's one thousand tomorrows, or three thousand, or ten, so much time you can bathe in it, roll around it, let it slide like coins through you fingers. So much time you can waste it", "tags": ["inspirational-life"]}
{"author": "J.R.R. Tolkien", "text": "Fantasy is escapist, and that is its glory. If a soldier is imprisioned by the enemy, don't we consider it his duty to escape?. . .If we value the freedom of mind and soul, if we're partisans of liberty, then it's our plain duty to escape, and to take as many people with us as we can!", "tags": ["fantasy", "literature", "philosophy"]}
