{"author": "Nathaniel Hawthorne", "text": "A single dream is more powerful than a thousand realities.", "tags": []}
{"author": "Sarah Dessen", "text": "So you're always honest,\" I said", "tags": ["lies", "truth"]}
{"author": "Edna St. Vincent Millay", "text": "They say when you are missing someone that they are probably feeling the same, but I don't think it's possible for you to miss me as much as I'm missing you right now", "tags": ["longing", "love", "missing", "sadness"]}
{"author": "Robert Frost", "text": "A poem begins as a lump in the throat, a sense of wrong, a homesickness, a lovesickness.", "tags": ["poetry"]}
{"author": "J.D. Salinger", "text": "Among other things, you'll find that you're not the first person who was ever confused and frightened and even sickened by human behavior. You're by no means alone on that score, you'll be excited and stimulated to know. Many, many men have been just as troubled morally and spiritually as you are right now. Happily, some of them kept records of their troubles. You'll learn from them\u2014if you want to. Just as someday, if you have something to offer, someone will learn something from you. It's a beautiful reciprocal arrangement. And it isn't education. It's history. It's poetry.", "tags": ["antolini"]}
{"author": "Richard Feynman", "text": "Nobody ever figures out what life is all about, and it doesn't matter. Explore the world. Nearly everything is really interesting if you go into it deeply enough.", "tags": []}
{"author": "Audrey Niffenegger", "text": "Don't you think it's better to be extremely happy for a short while, even if you lose it, than to be just okay for your whole life?", "tags": ["life"]}
{"author": "Nora Ephron", "text": "Reading is escape, and the opposite of escape; it's a way to make contact with reality after a day of making things up, and it's a way of making contact with someone else's imagination after a day that's all too real.", "tags": ["reading"]}
{"author": "Lois Lowry", "text": "Take pride in your pain; you are stronger than those who have none", "tags": []}
{"author": "Italo Calvino", "text": "A classic is a book that has never finished saying what it has to say.", "tags": ["books", "classics", "literature", "meaning", "reading", "words"]}
{"author": "Christopher Paolini", "text": "Live in the present, remember the past, and fear not the future, for it doesn't exist and never shall. There is only now.", "tags": ["inspirational"]}
{"author": "J.R. Ward", "text": "Welcome to the wonderful world of jealousy, he thought. For the price of admission, you get a splitting headache, a nearly irresistable urge to commit murder, and an inferiority complex. Yippee.", "tags": ["humor", "jealousy", "love"]}
{"author": "Maurice Sendak", "text": "A book is really like a lover. It arranges itself in your life in a way that is beautiful.", "tags": []}
{"author": "Barbara Kingsolver", "text": "The very least you can do in your life is figure out what you hope for. And the most you can do is live inside that hope. Not admire it from a distance but live right in it, under its roof.", "tags": ["hope"]}
{"author": "Paulo Coelho", "text": "Remember that wherever your heart is, there you will find your treasure.", "tags": ["confidence", "honesty"]}
{"author": "Rainer Maria Rilke", "text": "Be patient toward all that is unsolved in your heart and try to love the questions themselves, like locked rooms and like books that are now written in a very foreign tongue. Do not now seek the answers, which cannot be given you because you would not be able to live them. And the point is, to live everything. Live the questions now. Perhaps you will then gradually, without noticing it, live along some distant day into the answer.", "tags": ["ambiguity", "virtue"]}
{"author": "C.S. Lewis", "text": "There are far, far better things ahead than any we leave behind.", "tags": []}
{"author": "Kurt Vonnegut", "text": "If I should ever die, God forbid, let this be my epitaph", "tags": ["blues", "god", "life", "music"]}
{"author": "Henry Van Dyke", "text": "Time i", "tags": []}
{"author": "Suzanne Collins", "text": "You here to finish me off, Sweetheart?", "tags": ["humor", "hunger-games", "katniss", "mellark", "peeta", "romance"]}
