{"author": "Chinua Achebe", "text": "If you don't like someone's story, write your own.", "tags": []}
{"author": "Clive Barker", "text": "Any fool can be happy. It takes a man with real heart to make beauty out of the stuff that makes us weep.", "tags": ["art", "inspirational", "love", "redemption", "sadness"]}
{"author": "C. JoyBell C.", "text": "We have to allow ourselves to be loved by the people who really love us, the people who really matter. Too much of the time, we are blinded by our own pursuits of people to love us, people that don't even matter, while all that time we waste and the people who do love us have to stand on the sidewalk and watch us beg in the streets! It's time to put an end to this. It's time for us to let ourselves be loved.", "tags": ["growing", "humanity", "inspirational", "inspirational-life", "inspirational-love", "inspirational-quotes", "learning", "life-and-living", "life-lessons", "love", "people", "real-love", "reality", "reality-of-life", "those-who-love-us", "to-be-loved", "true-love", "what-matters"]}
{"author": "Stewart O'Nan", "text": "You couldn't relive your life, skipping the awful parts, without losing what made it worthwhile. You had to accept it as a whole--like the world, or the person you loved.", "tags": ["acceptance", "life", "love", "worth"]}
{"author": "Haruki Murakami", "text": "Sometimes fate is like a small sandstorm that keeps changing directions. You change direction but the sandstorm chases you. You turn again, but the storm adjusts. Over and over you play this out, like some ominous dance with death just before dawn. Why? Because this storm isn't something that blew in from far away, something that has nothing to do with you. This storm is you. Somethin", "tags": []}
{"author": "Elizabeth Gilbert", "text": "Happiness is the consequence of personal effort. You fight for it, strive for it, insist upon it, and sometimes even travel around the world looking for it. You have to participate relentlessly in the manifestations of your own blessings. And once you have achieved a state of happiness, you must never become lax about maintaining it. You must make a mighty effort to keep swimming upward into that happiness forever, to stay afloat on top of it.", "tags": ["happiness"]}
{"author": "Christopher Paolini", "text": "Books should go where they will be most appreciated, and not sit unread, gathering dust on a forgotten shelf, don't you agree?", "tags": ["books", "reading"]}
{"author": "Benjamin Disraeli", "text": "There are three types of lies -- lies, damn lies, and statistics.", "tags": ["attributed-no-source", "lies", "lying", "misattributed-mark-twain", "statistics", "truth"]}
{"author": "Veronica Roth", "text": "I am selfish. I am brave.", "tags": []}
{"author": "S.E. Hinton", "text": "If you have two friends in your lifetime, you're lucky. If you have one good friend, you're more than lucky.", "tags": ["friends", "friendship"]}
