{"author": "Friedrich Nietzsche", "text": "There are no facts, only interpretations.", "tags": ["perspective", "truth"]}
{"author": "Aldous Huxley", "text": "After silence, that which comes nearest to expressing the inexpressible is music.", "tags": ["music"]}
{"author": "Colette", "text": "You will do foolish things, but do them with enthusiasm.", "tags": ["enthusiasm", "foolishness", "silliness", "wisdom"]}
{"author": "Cornelia Funke", "text": "Isn't it odd how much fatter a book gets when you've read it several times?\" Mo had said...\"As if something were left between the pages every time you read it. Feelings, thoughts, sounds, smells...and then, when you look at the book again many years later, you find yourself there, too, a slightly younger self, slightly different, as if the book had preserved you like a pressed flower...both strange and familiar.", "tags": ["books", "feelings", "reading", "thoughts"]}
{"author": "Nicholas Sparks", "text": "Life, he realize, was much like a song. In the beginning there is mystery, in the end there is confirmation, but it's in the middle where all the emotion resides to make the whole thing worthwhile.", "tags": ["life", "love", "music", "simile", "song"]}
