{"author": "Rick Riordan", "text": "Grover was sniffing the wind, looking nervous. He fished out his acorns and threw them into the sand, then played his pipes. They rearranged themselves in a pattern that made no sense to me, but Grover looked concerned", "tags": ["acorns", "percy-jackson", "zoe-nightshade"]}
{"author": "T.S. Eliot", "text": "For last year's words belong to last year's languag", "tags": ["language", "new-year", "voice", "words"]}
{"author": "Ernest Hemingway", "text": "There is nothing noble in being superior to your fellow man; true nobility is being superior to your former self.", "tags": ["humility", "self-improvement"]}
{"author": "Marilyn Monroe", "text": "It's often just enough to be with someone. I don't need to touch them. Not even talk. A feeling passes between you both. You're not alone.", "tags": ["feelings", "not-alone"]}
{"author": "Yann Martel", "text": "It is true that those we meet can change us, sometimes so profoundly that we are not the same afterwards, even unto our names.", "tags": []}
