{"author": "A.A. Milne", "text": "I knew when I met you an adventure was going to happen.", "tags": []}
{"author": "Coco Chanel", "text": "It\u2019s probably not just by chance that I\u2019m alone. It would be very hard for a man to live with me, unless he\u2019s terribly strong. And if he\u2019s stronger than I, I\u2019m the one who can\u2019t live with him. \u2026 I\u2019m neither smart nor stupid, but I don\u2019t think I\u2019m a run-of-the-mill person. I\u2019ve been in business without being a businesswoman, I\u2019ve loved without being a woman made only for love. The two men I\u2019ve loved, I think, will remember me, on earth or in heaven, because men always remember a woman who caused them concern and uneasiness. I\u2019ve done my best, in regard to people and to life, without precepts, but with a taste for justice.", "tags": ["autonomy", "bachelorhood", "empowerment", "freedom", "independence", "individuality", "love", "marriage", "matrimony", "men", "self-determination", "self-sufficiency", "singles", "strength", "women"]}
